# Windsurf Rules for The Vault
# Full context: AGENTS.md. Architecture decisions: docs/decisions/

## Cascade Behavior
- Before any multi-file edit, state which files will be touched and why.
- Respect the layer architecture from AGENTS.md. Parser never calls AI. Routes are thin.
- When generating new API endpoints, always generate the corresponding Pydantic schema.
- When editing the frontend, always generate the corresponding TypeScript type in lib/types.ts.

## Flow Rules
- Complete one logical change at a time. Do not refactor while adding features.
- If a change requires touching more than 5 files, pause and describe the plan first.
- Always run the affected test suite mentally before suggesting the change.

## Style
Same as .cursorrules — Google docstrings, Pydantic v2, typed hooks, named exports.

## Forbidden
Same as .cursorrules. No cloud APIs. No subprocess shell=True. No localStorage.